      %p Welcome to MetaFad, Inc. ("MetaFad," "we," "us" or "our"). MetaFad is a social voting application that allows you to share and consume media. Create a poll, snap a photo, and/or vote upon/add comments (if you like) to other user polls. MetaFad is designed to allow users to post photographs for public review and comment. By submitting your photograph and/or posting comments and/or voting, you waive any privacy expectations you have with respect to those photographs and/or comments and/or votes and to our use thereof. If you do not wish to have your picture, comments, or votes viewed by or disclosed to others, do not use the MetaFad application or MetaFad website.
      %p Our Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, share and protect information in relation to our mobile services, web site, and any software provided on or in connection with MetaFad services (collectively, the "Service"), and your choices about the collection and use of your information.
      %p By using our Service you understand and agree that we are providing a platform for you to post content, including photos, comments and other materials ("User Content"), to the Service and to share User Content publicly. This means that other Users may search for, see, use, or share any of your User Content that you make publicly available through the Service, consistent with the terms and conditions of this Privacy Policy and our Terms of Use (found at http://musememobile.com/legal/terms). 
      %p Our Policy applies to all visitors, users, and others who access the Service ("Users").
      %ol
        %li 
          %h3 INFORMATION WE COLLECT
          %p We collect the following types of information.
          %ul 
            %li 
              %b Information you provide us directly:
              %ul 
                %li Your username, password and e-mail address when you register for a MetaFad account.
                %li Profile information that you provide for your user profile (e.g., first and last name, picture). This information allows us to help you or others be "found" on MetaFad.
